You are debugging a production issue where a distributed Saga orchestrator invokes a downstream booking service. The booking service is annotated with Spring's `@Transactional` but is failing to roll back database changes when a custom checked `BookingException` is thrown. Below is the service implementation:

java
@Service
public class BookingService {
    @Autowired
    private InventoryRepository inventoryRepository;

    @Transactional
    public void reserveSeat(String bookingId) throws BookingException {
        inventoryRepository.updateStatus(bookingId, 'RESERVED');
        try {
            callExternalPaymentGateway(bookingId);
        } catch (IOException e) {
            throw new BookingException('Payment failed', e);
        }
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where an asynchronous pipeline processing user notifications silently ignores failures. Under heavy load, remote notification calls fail, but no exceptions are printed to the logs, nor does the system raise any alerts. You locate the following execution block:

java
public void processNotifications(List<Notification> targets) {
    targets.forEach(target -> {
        CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> remoteService.send(target))
            .thenApply(this::formatResponse)
            .thenAccept(dbService::logSuccess);
    });
}

You are debugging a production issue where fallback resilience mechanisms fail to execute. During an external API outage, a Spring Boot application using Resilience4j continues throwing raw connection timeout exceptions directly to clients instead of returning a cached fallback response. The developer implemented the following service class:

java
@Service
public class RemoteQueryService {

    public Map<String, Object> getDataWithFallback() {
        return queryExternalAPI(); 
    }

    @CircuitBreaker(name = 'apiBreaker', fallbackMethod = 'getFallbackData')
    public Map<String, Object> queryExternalAPI() {
        throw new RemoteServiceException('Connection failed!');
    }

    public Map<String, Object> getFallbackData(Throwable t) {
        return Map.of('status', 'cached_data');
    }
}
